reviews_data.review_text: Joined to bookshop. Cozy, kid friendly, main Street destination.
Great coffee, like the space.

Started coming here awhile ago, love the energy and drinks. I also thouroughly enjoy reading the review responses. They are so sassy in the best way. Love the humor the owner has!! Also my iced mocha latte today was very good.
My favorite coffee shop I do all my meetings here and enjoy everything on their menu. The owners are the sweetest humans!
Amazing coffee and treats. One of my favorite coffee spots not just in Concord but CLT as well! Staff are awesome and so are some of the treats!
Such a cute spot. Love this little place! Great vibes, great coffee :)
It's always a cozy spot to meet the family for a coffee and snack. My granddaughter loves the small play shop in the back.
Went here for the first time with a friend and loved the coffee! Got the mocha and its probably the best around. Love the atmosphere

So thankfull Press and Porter has remained open during the construction!
The dirty Chai is perfect!
Such a cool gem! Great coffee options Ms a chill atmosphere. Definitely try. Main Street construction reducing foot traffic so definitely support the local businesses.  5 stars!!

I went in with a friend and everyone looked at us like we needed to get out. They barely acknowledged us to take our order. And the coffee is so small for the price, and  tasted like watered down coffee with no sweetness at all.

I'm currently away from my North Carolina home for a month and all I can think every time I visit a coffee shop here is "Dang, this is SO not as good as Press & Porter." and find myself disappointed! When I'm at home I frequent this place twice weekly (at LEAST) and the coffee is just FANTASTIC! It's run with such care and you always get the friendliest service. I miss their mocha latte and their cinnamon bun cold brew... you best bet as soon as I make it home, this is going to be my first stop again! Love ya Press & Porter!
Great coffee and great service! Love small coffee shops and their vibe and this place delivered on that!
Great service.  Great coffee.  Great location.

My BFF and I drove by to grab some iced coffee, and OMG it's heaven in your mouth!
I got the Zoe with a caramel drizzle. It was so unbelievably bursting with flavor. Press and Porter is definitely a favorite place of mine now. Service is outstanding, and wait time on delivery of order is quite fast paced. Parking was a little bit of a challenge, we waited for a spot to open. Although it was worth the wait!

If you are looking for a magical coffee run, drop by and try out them out! You will love the entire experience.

My kids and I come here every week and are always greeted like family! Not only is the coffee, food and service great, but they are constantly making my kids feel special and welcome with the child friendly area! My son loved to look at the construction going on out the front window so they created a construction play area! My daughter loves to go on our "coffee dates" and is so excited to wear her new shirt!
Great drinks. My go to coffee spot.
Great coffee, great service, and fun staff!

I've been going to Press and porter since they opened. They've always had amazing staff and coffee. What I love most about Press and Porter is that when my son and I would go in, they would remember his "coffee". Whenever he was learning how to pay for his own items, they patiently waited for him to be finished paying. The children's area is always a hit. Whenever you're done drinking coffee at press and porter, head over to Goldberry's books or not just Franks.
Such a cute spot to have in downtown Concord! Great coffee and the pastries are delicious.

A wonderful coffee shop with delicious coffee and baked goods. I highly recommend coming here for play dates with your kids! They have a play area with books, a play kitchen, construction toys, and more that my daughter loves. It's a great place to spend time and make memories. The caramel macchiato and the oatmeal cookies are the best!
Love this little coffee shop! My husband and I go there at least once a week. Great coffee, seating and atmosphere. The baristas are always cheerful and pleasant to talk to!
My home away from home when I was in nursing school! Everyone is always so kind and welcoming. A staple in the community!
Such a great shop. Great coffee and good people. Perfect for working, bringing the littles, or a coffee date!

Best coffee shop in dtc! Love how friendly the staff is, and they're always crafting drinks to perfection. Emily and Anna (owners) are a powerhouse sister duo and it's a joy to stop in or come hang out and get some work done. They are welcoming of my whole (rowdy!) family, and their playlists are always spot on. My kids love to go to the library and then to "their coffee shop"!

Truly my favorite small business in Concord. A shop filled with people who love this town, people that know your name, appreciate your business and they make a mean cup. Press and Porter is part of why I love my town.

Favorite coffee spot in the area! The service is always welcoming and accommodating to my four children. I've never had a bad drink and the seasonal menu is always a treat. There is plenty of cozy seating for one-on-one meetings, working alone, hanging with a group, or taking the kids for a reading day. Lots of easy options for parking, even with the never ending construction on Union St.
So thankful to live in walking distance of this little piece of home.

This is my favorite local coffee shop! Their coffee is consistently great, and I love that they have fun seasonal drinks. They always remember my coffee order!  It is soooo cute and welcoming.  They have delicious pastries and treats, and I love that they have lunch options too!
The ladies that run this place have been through so much hardship with construction shutting down their front/main entrance, but they still show up every day with smiles on their faces. Try it out and support local!!!
One of THE best coffee spots in Concord. Cozy atmosphere if you want to sit and stay a while, and great service.

I absolutely adore this coffee shop! I always get a caramel and coconut latte and it's the best one around!! I love that they are so toddler/child friendly! Even with the mess that downtown concord is currently this coffee shop still has a welcoming vibe!
Delicious coffee and friendly service. They have the perfect little area to entertain my littles while I have momma time and enjoy my coffee. They also have drink and treats the kids love!
Perfect spot for crying and losing my mind, no one judged and coffee was good
Press and Porter is the bomb! Come here often with my son when in the area. Highly recommend!

We first started frequenting P&P in late 2021, and has become a weekly (often multiple times a week) tradition for us. The coffee and espresso is incredible. The drink menu is vast and well developed and we have ordered "off menu" to great success. There is a "favorites" menu from baristas and locals that has some unique and wonderful drinks on it. The pastries and quick bites are very good. Try an affogato on a hot summer afternoon or a gingerbread latte in the winter, you won't be disappointed.

The baristas are welcoming, professional, and highly skilled. The owners take incredible care of the shop, keep the menu fresh and exciting, and have always delivered a great experience. We love the feeling of community when we come in to visit.

I used to take advantage of the free (and fast!) Wi-Fi to complete my coursework and study for exams. I never had trouble finding a table and an outlet to myself or to share with someone else doing computer work. The noise level is what you would expect for a community coffee house. It has plenty of comfortable seating to relax and hang out in. Board games are available upon request, and there are plenty of books and toys for the younger ones.

Despite the construction woes, P&P has stayed a beacon of the community and is a powerful voice in the push to shop (and drink great coffee!) small.

So grateful to have this amazing spot in downtown Concord. We walk down here very weekend, and I enjoy it so much every time. The drinks are phenomenal, the staff is always so kind and helpful, and the atmosphere is so fun and chill. Definitely one of my favorite coffee shops in the area.
Great vibes, would recommend
Favorite local coffee, welcomes the whole family
Delicious coffee, friendly staff, cozy atmosphere!
My latte is always great, plenty of milk alternatives<3 love it, it my go to shop

Almost a daily customer here and it's always a great atmosphere and friendly owners and baristas. I'm a difficulty coffee order and they get me spot on every time and even check to make sure its right. Also, usually super quick service!! Go support this small business!

One of my favorite places to go and enjoy a coffee while working or reading or just plain chilling out.  They have wonderful coffee selections throughout the year, so keep checking for the next surprise!   Press and Porter has done an amazing job of overcoming the adversity of the Downtown construction "progress"!
Press and Porter is our go to coffee spot here in Concord! We love it - such good coffee and good company.

Don't live in the CLT metro anymore but when I did, I happily drove from Dilworth to Concord just for visits to Press & Porter plus Goldberry Books next door - the combo can't be beat! Love the drip coffee and baked goods, and my husband's faves are iced lattes and breakfast sandwiches. Everything is always tasty and the atmosphere is awesome - especially welcoming to families with young kiddos!! Have visited the area a few times since moving away and always prioritize a trip to Press & Porter
Love this place! Every drink I've tried has been amazing! The atmosphere is perfect and the baristas are always so kind :)

A vanilla iced chai with oat milk and a pastry, can't go wrong! If anything it's a race to find seating (which is crazy cause there's a lot!) on the weekends! Lots of outlets as well for people like me who bring their laptops to work. And the fact that it's connected to Goldberry is always a plus :)
After consistently delivering great coffee, the friendliest service and the most comfortable community vibe in the area, this is still my favorite coffee shop anywhere.
One of my favorite coffee shops in this area!! Love the vibe, the comfy places to sit, and the welcoming atmosphere

I've been coming to Press and Porter for years. It's an amazing place with many different seating areas for quiet time by yourself or for larger studying groups. It's family friendly with a kids play cart in the back and a construction viewing area in the front. The drinks are inventive (like the Goldberry and Chaider) and even the standards are wonderful (they have the best lavender honey latte in town). The staff are friendly and knowledgeable, always willing to help you make a decision. And the food is top notch. I love the spicy garlic bagel and the breakfast sandwiches.

Everytime I walk in, it's just a delight!! The coffee is always amazing, definitely one of my Top 3 Coffee places EVER! The shop is just such a comfortable vibe and I just love that you can walk right into the bookstore as well (coming from a coffee and book lover, this makes the perfect combo!!). I also love that they work with other local businesses, I had the pesto pasta that was just INCREDIBLE. The workers are also super sweet, never had a bad experience. Keep up the good work
Cozy and delicious!
Community comes first here. If you step foot in this shop, you're treated as family. Bright atmosphere with exceptional brew that's sure to be one of the best parts of your day.

The best coffee shop in concord and maybe anywhere! We love how friendly the owners and baristas are and it feels like home when we walk in. Don't sleep on their chai; it's the best I've ever had! They support other local businesses and have really cultivated a sense of community.

I love coming to this cozy coffee shop. A place where the baristas get to know you.
I also love their kid area.
Perfect place to meet people or hang out solo!

Press & Porter is an amazing coffee shop in Downtown Concord! From the decor, to the seating arrangements, to the amazing personalities of those who make your drinks, you can't go wrong stopping in to fuel up! Don't like coffee? There's options for everyone! Everything there's done with intention. Their survival through Covid & downtown construction is a testament to their presence in our town.

This is one of the coffee shops I always recommend in Concord! I think they do a great job at catering to ALL customers. There's always a little area for kids, plenty of different seating-chairs, couches, tables. Grab a chai tea, specialty latte, or a grab and go lunch
Love this place. Perfect for getting some work done, catching up with friends, or just enjoying some quiet time to yourself. Coffee and food are both great. Love the giant oatmeal cream pies!

One of my favorite local spots. The coffee is good, and the vibes are always great. For the record, I have never sat in an uncomfy chair. I can vouch that the atmosphere, coffee, and seating is all top tier. Keep pressing on :)! (Pun intended)
Amazing coffee and vibes
Chairs uncomfortable
Lame ahh coffee

Update -- same great coffee and friendly baristas. Today's coffee of choice was "The Gerald". Perfect!

A good cup of coffee on Sunday morning on the way to church. Be sure to check the chalkboard for the drink specials. The "J.J." was especially good!

I have tried this place 4 times now because I really wanted to like it. The shop is very homey and relaxing and there is a bookstore right next door so it's perfect for grabbing a new book and then sitting down to a coffee... however,  the coffee and the food taste terrible and at my last visit everything was inedible! Every drink variation I have tried so far has tasted burnt or just lacked flavor. The bakery items have been okay but again the last time I was there it took 30 minutes to make my breakfast sandwich and it came out cold, greasy, and tasted terrible. I didn't even eat half of it before I decided it was nothing but trash. I've decided to give up on this place.  Thankfully another coffee shop has now opened up in the area and so far has been a much better option.

Great atmosphere. Very clean and cozy. Hot breakfast sandwiches are baked so need 10 minutes, but it's sooooo much better than Starbucks. Coffee is great too. Just as good as the other place though there are not as many ultra high sweet coffees.

I had the bacon, egg and cheese croissant and wife had the most wonderful warm coffee cake.

Great dirty chai and my Americano was great.
Had a peppermint hot chocolate, was warm not hot. Was halfway full. Daughter didn't want me to say anything. She likes going there with freinds
They make a mean macchiato, so good. Cozy spot for a catch up with friends
Their OG dark brew is my reason for getting out of bed in the morning.
Been coming here for years and it's a great place to get coffee and talk
We came during the candy crawl. It was wonderful and cozy. Our drinks were very good.

We stopped in there today during the Concord Candy Crawl, We order hot Chocolate and Latte's, they were served room temperature. We waited over 20 minutes for the drinks to be made since they only had 1 person making the drinks. I asked if my latte can be microwave since it wasnt even warm and the girl seemed annoyed. $25 for 5 cold drinks, Very disappointing!

So this review is done solely on a drip cup of coffee but fantastic service! As fate would have it I finished run this morning and the power was out in the city of Concord. I took a chance and walked into the coffee shop because the open sign was up. There were no lights on in the place but I was greeted with hello can we help you. I said you guys have coffee and the answer was yes and I said I would love some coffee just a cup with a little bit of cream.
So that's what I got. And it was awesome! Thank you so much.

Everytime my sisters and I come home from college, Press and Porter is where we look forward to coming. Best staff, amazing food and coffee, and a small-town "homey" feel here. We love playing the board/card games in the back and just enjoying the space.
Due to construction  by the DOT the parking was tricky, but you know what, totally worth it. Our first time and most definitely NOT the last.
The Zoe drink is the best. Love press and porter!
Very good coffee and friendly staff. It's also very spacious and has plenty of seating.

Fantastic place to study, hang out at, or grab something yummy on the go. There was plenty of seating for a variety of group sizes and great table space. The staff were friendly and the coffee was good. Definitely recommend an iced Irish cream latte. Not too sweet and balanced, so you could still taste and enjoy the coffee flavor as well as the syrup
Fantastic place for community and reading.

Hate even giving this communist establishment a 1 star rating... Most unpatriotic in American establishment I've ever been to. Over priced and over rated
.
Delicious and cheap
Cute spot! Great hot and cold lattes, fast wifi, and parking around back!
This place is hands down the best spot around to get fresh coffee (of any kind) and elaborate homemade treats. The staff is always friendly and helpful with questions.
One of my favorite coffee shops! I got a iced matcha with coconut syrup and milk and it was the best matcha I've ever had. Hade a place for kids In the back. I really enjoyed it (:
Coffee great
The best coffee and snacks! Comfy, cozy environment the relax and chill. Awesome staff! Highly recommended!
Good coffee
Super friendly staff! Affordable and tasty products!

It's SO cute in here!! We came in the back way which was a little different with the hallways, but the aesthetic is just perfect! They do have toys and games for the kids and great coffee and latte options. I even got a special blueberry coffee that tastes delicious.

Just started going into Press and Porter as we are new to the area. This place is great!! Both the girls that work in the morning are wonderful and the coffee is fantastic! I have been searching for a place to write my current novel that gives me the right vibe and this place delivers! Would recommend in a heartbeat!
I own a shop downtown and this is the first place I head after opening. The owner and everyone she hires are great. And most importantly their coffee is wonderful. I recommend an iced vanilla Lata.
Super nice service, just a little lacking in the pastry / food areas and coffee quality. Not bad coffee, but could've been better. Definitely a nice vibe inside though.
I just received one of the best extra dry cappuccinos that I've gotten from Layla. Great coffee shop. Love the comfortable couches and chairs.

Press and Porter is like my second home at this point! I'm here working a couple of days during the week and going on a coffee date with my husband on weekends. I like that they have a punch card system since I'm here so often hehe. The vibe is the best of all the coffee shops in Concord. You can have your own little area  to hang out or work because the way the couches and tables are sectioned out is brilliant. They also donated coffee and stickers to a community raffle for a nonprofit I'm part of which was really nice. They also have an adorable little childrens area with books, games, and a kids coffee cart!
Amazing experience. Everyone was very nice and the cheddar bacon croissant sandwich was amazing! Highly recommend this place to study at and grab a bite to eat :)
Went for a pour over. The "baristas" didn't even know what that is much less how to make one. Settled for the drip coffee which tasted old and bland. Didn't finish it. Will not be returning.

I come to this coffee shop when I'm in town. Today I came in and waited in line. There was a woman and gentlemen in front of me. While she was giving her order, another man and woman came in and got in line behind me. Apparently, the people in front of me where meeting up with the people behind me. The lady in front of me invited them to get in front of me and, at first, they refused. The lady continued to give her order and again invited the couple behind me to get in front of me, which at this point, they did. The lady that invited them to get in front of me turned and said to me "They're with me: Sorry". The cashier paused and looked at them and me and then took the order of the two people that had gotten in front of me. I normally have a great experience at this coffee shop (and would probably still recommend them) But this experience left a bad taste in my mouth.

The cashier taking the two other people's order before mine caused a long wait for me: which is in the control of the shop. I would have just said something while I was there but I've been struggling with aphasia and talking in public can be embarrassing sometimes. So going to places where I can type out my order and show it makes things easier. But trying to type out why I don't think someone else should be allowed to get in front of me, shouldn't be necessary.
This place has amazing vibes and incredible lattes!!! Layla was super friendly and made the experience so much fun!!!
I love this place. I come at least a few times a week. Staff is always so friendly and the coffee is always a hit. Also the homemade bagels are delicious
Great little coffee shop in downtown Concord. It's next to a book store as well that one should check out.
Very good coffee and drinks and the service was excellent
It is a nice slice of the cafe life in a fast  food wasteland and instant coffee of the southern bland.

Comfy. Warm. Yummy. Affordable. Local.
All things we should all look for in a coffee shop! And it's right here in downtown Concord with street or deck parking in convenient reach!

Step away from corporate coffee. I promise, this is worth it.

Very friendly and welcoming staff and a extremely cozy interior and great drinks at the average price range for local owned shops and chains in the same caliber. One thing that makes this coffee shop stand out is its location with the book store next door being connected by a hallway and a parking garage right down the street!
What a great find...reqlly nice place with fast friendly service. I will be back often!
Most quiet coffee shop I've ever been. Got a hot apple-chia-der. It was amazing! The chai scone was also delicious. Didn't think there was a coffee shop downtown. Glad to find it.
Excellent to work and bring your kiddos
A great place to get a coffee. The service is always excellent.  Also, a book store next door to dip into.
First visit today - delicious iced latte and plenty of yummy baked goods. Great vibe and very kid friendly. Will definitely be back!!
Friendly atmosphere, chill vibe and great drinks!! I often have drinks here with my clients
Not a coffee drinker, was with friends. Must say it was hoppin while we were there and the environment was quite charming.

Fresh coffee, wide selection of drinks. Drinks way too sweet for me but kindly advised this was the case and drinks were happily remade free of charge even though I offered to pay. Lots of beans to pick from for coffee at home as well.
Great place for your favorite caffeine fix or tea.
Much better than I remember! It was hopping at 10:30 in the morning and I think the furniture is much more comfortable. Many interesting drink suggestions...
Boujee vibes and bomb coffee, probably the go to from now on.
Cute little place. The cold brew was good. Nice environment and I like that they had a few books on the table that I could read while I waited.

Awesome vibes and great coffee. I love this place.
They also have live music every once in a while.
We love the families behind this company as much as the product and service. Local coffee in the cutest downtown! Must visit if you are swinging through concord!

This was my first time at this Coffee House and the experience was really relaxing. The vybe was really chill and the customer service was exemplary! I had a Italian soda blood orange flavor!! Highly recommend!!

Love, love, love the vibe here!

I stopped here while passing visiting Concord's historic district for my first time. It was raining outside and I was looking for a cozy, little local stop with character. The drinks, of course, are great. But even more important for me is the atmosphere. Everyone here seems to know each other and lots of folks are working here well enjoying a hot beverage.

Personally I love this vibe and I will choose it any day over Starbucks or a big box coffee shop.  Concord is lucky to have this treasure!
Very reasonable pricing for delicious coffee drinks! Lots of seating space and a cute area for kids and reading. Love it!

Press & Porter is the most charming place for coffee, kombucha, and local craft beers! They have always been very kind and friendly and when I reached out to them for a private event, they were more than welcoming and accommodating for every question and need I had. The event turned out wonderfully and everyone enjoyed our time there. The place is already so nicely decorated and had plenty of flexible seating and tables and they even helped me rearrange furniture. I couldn't have asked for a better experience or atmosphere for this very special occasion/celebration! Anna & Emily have created such a beautiful place and brand! Everyone should visit Press & Porter!!

This was the worst place I have ever been. Myself along with my husband and our brother who are all veterans went there to get a cup of coffee and charge up and   And Got the COPS called on us telling us needed to leave and are band from there. The reason was cause we were making customers feel uncomfortable and blocked the bathrooms when we were out of the way and let people know that there was an open bathroom on the other side where we were. WOW 3 VETERANS WHO SEVERED THIS COUNTRY TOLD WE ARE BANDED FROM THERE CAUSE WE BOUGHT COFFEE AND WHERE CHARGING UP OUR STUFF LIKE EVERYONE ELSE THERE WAS.  These people are nothing but a joke and the fact that we spent $9 for 3 small coffees was the the worst part before that. Unless you have lots of money to spend don't go here it's not worth it.
I always get a hot mocha and coffee cake to share! The coffee cake is enough for two and is super moist and delicious!

Amazing little shop that popped up as a suggestion when I asked my phone to find the best local coffee house. Great choice, Google! I was NOT disappointed. The service was friendly and had great suggestions. I ended up getting a "Black Nitro" cold brew with a scoop of vanilla bean ice cream on top. The cold brew was definitely nitro. Full octane rocket fuel! I like strong coffee but this stuff was strong strong strong. I cannot remember ever (EVER!) not being able to finish a coffee, until now. Wow! If anyone can finish that and sleep within 12hrs I'm impressed. Anyway, great place and I'm eager to try it again next time I'm in town.
Very cute ambience and my friend swears by the London fog but I prefer the mocha
Good drinks, great atmosphere, and next to a locally owned bookstore. What an awesome place.
My office away from home, or is that vice versa

Great experience! We were greeted by a sweet young lady that made us two vanilla lattes. This coffee shop offers wine as well. We will try the treats the next time we visit. I took pics of the baked goods including bagels and English muffins.
Earlier, we had gone to the Gibson Mill Antique Mall & decided to explore downtown Concord since it is nearby. Pleasantly Surprised by the selection of shops: from an established French Bakery, Italian and Cuban restaurants to the cutest bookstore next door to the coffee shop. Make it a day- start out at the huge antique mall and wrap it up in downtown Concord. Supporting local is so much fun!

The staff is really kind, cool decoration, good environment.
I got a vanilla latte with Irish cream, yummy!
Local coffee house with nice selection and friendly service.
Love this place. Comfy seating. Kid friendly but quiet enough to do work. Always pleasant. And of course great coffee
OMG best coffee ever!
Best coffee in Concord
If you walking downtown Concord and feel like you need coffee  chill enjoy music and some sweet treats this is it!!
Great strong brews and good local brew selection

Walked in for a quick drink. Place is cute and looks like a dope place to sit and chill. Educated me on a beverage allowed me to enjoy a sample and I left work a frozen dessert and a Pineapple Kombucha! I'll give it a shot if it was anything like the sample it will be great!

Alright y'all...it's time to quit that corporate coffee life and venture to the adorable little Press and Porter Coffee Shop in downtown Concord. I cannot express how lovely not only the atmosphere and coffee is but also the staff! These wonderful humans are always so positive and happy to create whatever concoction of morning life juice you are feeling!

Just an example of how awesome they are:

This morning I went to get an iced carmel machiatto and after I took a few sips...I quickly realized this drink was a little too sweet for me... Not wanting to make a scene but equally thirsting for a morning treat...I politely asked if they would be willing to remake the drink for me with a few less pumps of sweetener... Instantly, joyfully, and sincerely one of the ladies gladly insisted on doing so and said "We would rather you be happy !"

AHHH!!!!! GOOD VIBES...go here asap and support this amazing local business! <3 :)
Nice atmosphere and excellent service. Great place to have a delicious coffee and relax a little. I totally recommend it!
Super quaint, clean Place very nice atmosphere excellent coffee and tees. Pastries are unbelievably delicious
Fantastic coffee! Friendly service! Great small town atmosphere! Stop in for a cup of...coffee.
Disappointed by the lack of service.

I work on Union street and I'm really relieved there's a good coffee shop in walking distance. I love the interior and the vibe is amazing. They have several indoor and outdoor seating options. I've only tried the latte but they have different flavors and a variety of different beverages to try hot or cold! The service was excellent and the staff is super nice! Stop by soon!
Stopped in for an afternoon affogato.  Fantastic pick me up. Pleasant atmosphere.
Very clean , nice employees. Peaceful atmosphere.
The staff are always so gracious and personable. The drinks were great: I even started drinking the iced matcha.
Delicious craft coffee. I loved my coconut latte.
Local spot. Had a really good peach bar and an iced caramel and coconut latte. I don't like coconut but it was really good. Definitely glad I stopped in.
Great coffee shop! The staff is great, service is quick, and the place is so cute on the inside! And bonus they have a good Carmel syrup! I am super picky about Carmel flavors but I love theirs.
Good coffee place with an amazing local atmosphere that makes an out-of-towner like me feel right at home.

The owners + staff are always to kind + gracious. We frequently visit + are never disappointed in the service + quality. Major bonus that they're family friendly. It's our boys favorite stop on our walks!

Press and Porter is an amazing local gem. While their hours and customer service can be hit or miss sometimes, I have never had a bad coffee from them. The interior is VERY nice, modern, cozy, and a nice place to be. The fall flavors, especially the pumpkin pie latte, are to die for! Their baked treats that they get from local bakers are also very good! I would recommend stopping here.

EDIT: Their hours are much more consistent and better now. Also, Carson the barista is awesome!
Love this little shop! I've been living in downtown concord for 4 years and this coffee is the best! Love that it's a quick walk away and love their delicious drinks and treats!

My wife and I absolutely adore this place! One of the best additions to downtown Concord since we've moved here. They have a great selection of coffees with a seasonal rotating menu. Amazingly friendly staff with a very welcoming environment!
Good coffee and good service.  I was just in the neighborhood and stopped in to check them out.
Great people Great coffee Great place i like it
We came in after eating dinner and it was wonderful. Super cute inside, friendly staff, good coffee. Milk alternatives like soy and almond milk available!!

Charming little coffee shop! I drove through the area on a family vacation and stopped for a quick cup of coffee. I was not disappointed! If I was a local this would definitely be my "go-to" spot for coffee. Warm and inviting with a skilled barista behind the counter!
Great local cup of heaven, I mean iced coffee. Bold brew done very well. Great flavor without the bitterness. Timely, friendly service. A quite pleasant store ambience.
Nice chill atmosphere. Loved the eggnog latte and the mocha.

Press & Porter is the perfect addition to downtown Concord, paired nicely with Goldberry Books next door. My wife and I have made it a tradition to stop here on weekend mornings for coffee and a nibble. We love the excellent quality of the brews, the trendy and comfortable interior, and the nice folks working behind the counter. Highly recommended!
Staff was very friendly! Amazing coffee!
Good coffee. Nice atmosphere
A quaint coffee shop that offers a tranquil vibe, great service and pleasant relaxing atmosphere with most importantly great coffee!
Absolutely amazing atmosphere. Great drinks. Love coming here to read/write:)
Went to downtown concord on a relaxing Sunday morning, thankful they were open unlike others. Nice coffee and good vibe.
Love
I love press and porter! They are so nice and the matcha is really good. Now you can order from an app, which is super easy.
It was my first time there, I definitely will be returning, very clean bright place with a great atmosphere.
The London Fog was SOooo goood!!!
Delicious matcha. Soothing environment. Awesome friendly and knowledgable barista.
Quaint little coffe shop. Limited drinks but awesome little local spot to relax with a coffee.

I love this place! I go to press and Porter 4 times a week(at least), and it never gets old! Love the ladies that work there, and especially love their coffee! They are affordable and the atmosphere is great!

First in this establishment the girl behind the counter was not very welcoming. Ordered my drink started small talk with people. Found out she was an owner made a statement she was young to be an owner went downhill from there. Won't go back.

Having been a barista it's hard to find coffee I don't hate, especially when we're surrounded by mass retail coffee shops. I'm so happy that this opened up so close to home. The owners and baristas are all really kind and the coffee seems to be consistent in taste no matter who makes it. Doesn't matter how many times I go here, I'm always blown away by the taste. It's not overpriced, which is definitely a plus. I'm hoping that there might be more syrup flavors added at some point, but it doesn't detract from the experience. I think my favorite part about this place- and I have many favorite parts- is their specials. I like trying drinks I've never thought I'd like, only to be surprised by how good it is. They had this amazing sweet potato drink in the fall which really stood out to me. I don't even like sweet potato, and it seemed so weird to have in coffee, but I ordered it every time I visited while they had it. It's just a great place. I'm so happy we have this gem.
Amazing coffee!  We will definitely be back!

Can't wait until they have beer on draft! Great chai, atmosphere and music
Great cup of coffe and friendly service.  Nice inside. Wife liked her hot chocolate too.
Very Good coffee. Very relaxing.
Board games, couches, mini stage and several tables. Delicious dark blend and hot chocolates.
Awesome environment and Saturday Night music. The coffee is a little inconsistent but it's a new place so I have high hopes!
Love this place. Always friendly service most importantly the coffee is amazing. Very comfy environment as well.

This is THE BEST coffee shop in the area. And I mean including Kannapolis, Salisbury, and Concord. Their drinks are always made with care and attention. Their friendly staff makes the trip even better. The shop itself is made beautifully with plenty of seating and even counter seating near the espresso machine. As a Barista of nearly 10 years this is a great spot to get excellent coffee.
We just love having this coffee shop in downtown Concord.
Best coffe in town and Saturday they have awesome live music 10 out of 10
Love that they have vegan options from wander and whisk! Cute shop. Quiet for working. Can't wait to keep going back.
Awesome little spot in downtown Concord!  Their coffee is amazing and the staff is very friendly.  Perfect place to sit back and relax, work or meet up with friends or colleagues.  Highly recommend

It's such a cute place to come relax and enjoy delicious coffee and wine. The staff are always happy and willing to help guide your questions. The coffee is smooth tasting and never wavers in taste. Highly recommend!!

My new coffee spot. I love the slight bohemian vibe. Great music selection and the coffee is great. Also my wife and I brought our 4 year old in with ice cream from the creamer from across the street and the owners didn't mind. Super nice people and they had games as well.
A bright, clean, and open space with great coffee and friendly staff. Looking forward to their partnership with Downtown Donuts.

Love this new coffee shop! Nice collection of places to sit as an individual or if you are coming as a group! Kid friendly with a collection of kids books in the back. Coffee is great and smooth and they have a wide selection of drinks they make. Will be a regular stop for me!

I have been waiting for some delicious coffee in Downtown Concord and SO HAPPY with what Press & Porter have done to the shop! The cafe is so cozy and the coffee is fantastic! Come for a wake-up! Stay for the atmosphere! <3
Wonderful atmosphere in this quaint new cafe in Historic Downtown Concord! Drinks for adults and kids! Cute and cozy places to sit and work! This is the place for coffee in concord!
